# Privacy Policy — Runney

*Last updated: [DATE]*

## Overview

Runney ("the app") is designed to keep your data on your device. This policy explains
what data the app accesses, how it's used, and — just as importantly — what we *don't*
do with it.

## What data Runney accesses

Runney reads the following from Apple Health (HealthKit), with your explicit permission,
granted through Apple's standard Health access prompt:

- Running workouts (distance, duration, pace, route/GPS if recorded, heart rate, and
  active energy, where available)

Runney does **not** request permission to write or modify any data in Apple Health.

## What Runney stores

- Your running data, as read from Apple Health, is used **only on your device** to
  calculate your Stamina, Consistency, and Speed scores, level, badges, and personal
  records.
- App preferences (your name, chosen background color, distance unit, personal goals,
  race goal, and notification settings) are stored locally on your device using
  Apple's standard `UserDefaults` storage.

## What Runney does not do

- Runney does not create a user account and does not require sign-up or login.
- Runney does not send your health data, workouts, or any personal information to any
  server. There is no backend — all calculations happen on your device.
- Runney does not use third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.
- Runney does not share, sell, or transfer your data to any third party.

## Notifications

If you choose to enable the optional weekly recap notification, Runney schedules a local
notification directly on your device using Apple's notification system. No data leaves
your device to make this happen.

## Data deletion

Because Runney doesn't store your data anywhere except your own device, deleting the app
removes all app-specific data (preferences, goals, cached calculations) immediately.
Deleting Runney does not affect your underlying data in Apple Health — that remains
managed by Apple's Health app, under your control there.

## Children's privacy

Runney is not directed at children and does not knowingly collect data from children.
Since the app does not collect any data beyond what stays on-device, no data is
collected from any user, regardless of age.

## Changes to this policy

If Runney's data practices change in a future update (for example, if a feature is added
that requires a server), this policy will be updated accordingly, and the "Last updated"
date above will reflect that.

